snippet: A Utah woman accused of killing six newborns could not recall exactly how many dead infants were in her home, and the body of at least one baby was covered in a chemical that smelled like iodine, according to documents.
abstract: Police say Megan Huntsman, Utah woman accused of killing six of her newborn babies and storing them in her garage, was confused as to exact number of dead infants that were in her home.
lead_paragraph: A Utah woman accused of killing six newborns could not recall exactly how many dead infants were in her home, and the body of at least one baby was covered in a chemical that smelled like iodine, according to documents.

headline.main: Utah: Woman Was Confused About Dead Babies in Garage
